result.execSummary:
All charges against Tyree Neville Green in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tyree Neville Green is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:28 PM Defendant Tyree Neville Green appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Allison Cogbill in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Michael Hoffman in court via video for defendant. Defendant provided current address. Attorney Hoffman received information, waives reading and pleads not guilty to count 2 and requests preliminary hearing to Count 1. State requests $250 cash bail. State notes juvenile criminal history. Attorney Hoffman requests signature bond given local ties and age. Defendant wishes to have a signature bond as he does not want this on his record and is still in high school. Court reviews defendant's juvenile record. Court orders $500 cash bail and $500 signature bond with no specific conditions.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 31, 2022 at 08:45 am.
